        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 3:54PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Wingdale, or 9 miles northwest of Pawling, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amenia, Millbrook, Millerton, Stanfordville, Wingdale, Dover Plains,
Beekman, Bethel, Smithfield, South Dover, Lithgow, Hoxie Corner,
Clove Valley, Poughquag, South Amenia, Billings, Shunpike, Pleasant
Ridge, Shekomeko, and Bains Corner.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
